The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Wednesday, November 20, 2002 				 Cuffy not in squad of XV
																								WI IN BANGLADESH 																								St Johns: Ridley Jacobs will captain West Indies on a tour to Bangladesh in the absence of Carl Hooper, who faces a knee operation, the selectors said Tuesday.																								Jacobs, the wicketkeeper-batsman, is vice-captain on the West Indies tour of India. Skipper Hooper is to undergo corrective surgery on his troubled knees in Australia.																								The selection panel omitted fast bowler Cameron Cuffy from the 15-strong squad named Tuesday for three limited-overs Internationals and two Tests.																								Daren Ganga takes Hoopers place in the squad. Darren Powell, chosen in preference to Cuffy, has made only limited appearances in India.																								The ODIS																								Chittagong  November 29; 																								Dhaka (D/N)  December 2 and 3.																								The TestS																								Dhaka  December 8 to 12; 																								Chittagong  December 16 to 20.																								THE squad																								Ridley Jacobs (captain), Shivnarine Chanderpaul, Pedro Collins, Corey Collymore, Mervyn Dillon, Vasbert Drakes, Daren Ganga, Chris Gayle, Wavell Hinds, Jermaine Lawson, Mahendra Nagamootoo, Darren Powell, Ricardo Powell, Marlon Samuels, Ramnaresh Sarwan. (REUTERS)
